{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01Q9y51z4rjWPU17Xo9DWWrj","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"All goals met. Here's a summary of what was wrong and what was fixed:\n\n**Root cause — two bugs in the `rabbitmq-setup` job:**\n\n1. **Missing configure permission**: The setup job set `\"configure\":\"\"` (empty string = no configure access) for `app-user` on the `/app` vhost. Queue declaration is a _configure_ operation, so every `PUT /api/queues/%2Fapp/app-queue` returned `403 Access refused`. Fixed by setting `\"configure\":\".*\"`.\n\n2. **`force-quorum` policy** (defense-in-depth): The setup job also pushed a policy forcing all queues to `queue-type: quorum` on both `/` and `/app`. The producer declares `x-queue-type: classic`, which would conflict with that policy once the permission was fixed. Both policies were deleted (they were already absent in this run, but the fix handles them).\n\n**Final state:**\n- `app-producer` — `1/1 Running`, 0 restarts after fix\n- `app-queue` in `/app` vhost — type `classic`, 87 messages with a steady publish rate of ~0.6 msg/s\n- 3-node cluster (`rabbitmq-0/1/2`) — all `Running`, all in cluster state `running`"}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":309,"cache_read_input_tokens":46052,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":309},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"0a1f5e8a-4307-43cd-a3d6-52110567492e","uuid":"bffe4b0a-037b-434a-abee-a64ffb789bde","request_id":"req_011CbyEWrM9wmzkXp7RBjriJ"}
